  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd  \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf  \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bc7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Inside the President's House, where a large number of Sri Lankans are now found",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Rasmi Kavindaya says that she never dreamed of entering the President's House in her lifetime.",
        "Thousands like Kavinthaya flocked to see the mansion the day after protesters entered Sri Lanka's most protected building.",
        "It is a magnificent piece of colonial architecture with many corridors, rooms, a swimming pool and a beautiful lawn.",
        "Kavindaya, who came to the President's House with her four-year-old children, said, \"Look at the richness of this place.\"",
        "He mentioned that we live in a small village in a small house and this place is for people. He also mentioned that it was built with people's money.",
        "Thousands of men, women and children try to enter the area and some of the demonstrators discipline them.",
        "People going from room to room want to record the moments by taking selfies as they stand in front of the teak wood tables paintings rooms.",
        "Broken beams, broken desks, broken windows, etc. are scattered around. They are seen as reminders of the chaos that prevailed after people entered.",
        "Seeing this place is like a dream for me, says AL Premavardhana, who works at the children's park in Kanemulla.",
        "\"We used to wait in long queues for gas fueled food but it seems the Rajapaksas have lived a different life,\" he said.",
        "The leader of the protestors said that they will not leave their official gates until the President and the Prime Minister resign.",
        "The military and police stood idly by despite the pushback as people jostled to see the buildings. Meanwhile the activists of protest movements disciplined the people.",
        "The swimming pool itself has attracted much attention. Families stand near the swimming pool and watch it. The bystanders clapped and cheered when a young man jumped into it.",
        "Nirosa Sudarsini Hutchinson, who was there with her two teenage daughters, said, \"I am worried.\"",
        "A democratically elected president was forced to exit in disgrace. Shame on us for voting for him. He mentioned that the people want them to return the money they looted from the country.",
        "All three languages \u200b\u200bof Sri Lanka could be heard in the corridors. The excitement and interest of the visitors was evident.",
        "Hundreds of people, Buddhists, Christians and Hindus were seen outside the palace on a beautifully manicured lawn.",
        "Sri Lankans feel their months-long struggle has finally led to the removal of their country's leaders responsible for the economic collapse. A glimpse of the lifestyle of their leaders enrages them even more."
      ],
